    • put

      V put(K k, V v)
      Add a new key/value pair to the map. If the key already exists in the map, this method will replace its associated value, and return the value that was replaced.
      Parameters:
      k - The key to add.
      v - The value associated with k.
      Returns:
      The value formerly associated with k, if k was already in the map, null otherwise.
